# Sprint 3 — Pipeline Module

**Goal:** Sales + Credit Workflow Engine — track opportunities from lead to approval.

Per `CLAUDE_NEW.md` (Week 8–9), this module is 🔴 Critical for MVP.

## Scope

### Pipeline Stages (sequential, no skipping)
```
Lead → Initial Contact → Financial Collection → Analysis → Proposal → Committee → Approved / Rejected
```

### UI Layout
- **Primary View**: Kanban Board with drag-and-drop (`dnd-kit`)
- **Secondary View**: Table View (toggleable)
- **Filter Bar**: Stage · RM · Industry · Deal Value · Date Range
- **Opportunity Detail**: Side Drawer (activity feed, task checklist, document list, AI placeholder)

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **dnd-kit dependency**: The Kanban drag-and-drop requires `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable`. Should I install these?
> **Default answer: Yes** — proceeding unless you say otherwise.

## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Dependencies
- Install `@dnd-kit/core`, `@dnd-kit/sortable`, `@dnd-kit/utilities`

### 2. Types (`src/types/index.ts`)
New types:
- `PipelineStage` enum: `LEAD | INITIAL_CONTACT | FINANCIAL_COLLECTION | ANALYSIS | PROPOSAL | COMMITTEE | APPROVED | REJECTED`
- `PipelineOpportunity` interface: id, title, companyId, companyName, rmId, rmName, stage, dealValue, probability, notes, createdAt, updatedAt
- `PipelineActivity` interface: for the activity timeline
- `PipelineTask` interface: for the checklist

### 3. Mock Data (`src/lib/mock-data.ts`)
New functions:
- `getMockOpportunities(params?)` — filterable, paginated list
- `getMockOpportunityById(id)` — full detail with activities, tasks, documents
- `getMockPipelineSummary()` — deal counts and values per stage (for Kanban column headers)

### 4. Feature Hooks (`src/features/pipeline/hooks/`)
- `usePipeline.ts` — fetch opportunities with filter state
- `useOpportunity.ts` — fetch single opportunity detail

### 5. Pipeline List/Kanban Page (`/pipeline`)

#### [NEW] `src/features/pipeline/components/KanbanBoard.tsx`
- 8 columns (one per stage), drag-and-drop between stages using `@dnd-kit`
- Each card shows: Company name, Deal value, Probability badge, RM, alert count
- Column headers show deal count + total value
- `APPROVED` and `REJECTED` columns are terminal — cards dropped there trigger a confirmation

#### [NEW] `src/features/pipeline/components/KanbanCard.tsx`
- Draggable card component

#### [NEW] `src/features/pipeline/components/PipelineTable.tsx`
- TanStack table view of all opportunities
- Columns: Company, Title, Stage, Deal Value, Probability, RM, Last Updated

#### [NEW] `src/features/pipeline/components/PipelineFilters.tsx`
- View toggle (Kanban ↔ Table), search, stage/RM/industry filters

#### [NEW] `src/app/(dashboard)/pipeline/page.tsx`
- Assembles the page with filter bar and view toggle

### 6. Opportunity Detail Drawer (`/pipeline/[id]`)

#### [NEW] `src/features/pipeline/components/OpportunityDrawer.tsx`
- Sheet/drawer that slides in from the right when clicking a Kanban card or table row
- Left section: Stage progress indicator, company info, deal metadata
- Activity Timeline: list of logged activities with timestamps
- Task Checklist: items with checkbox state
- Document list: linked files placeholder

#### [NEW] `src/app/(dashboard)/pipeline/[id]/page.tsx`
- Standalone page for direct URL access to an opportunity

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation must pass.

### Manual Verification
- `/pipeline` renders the Kanban board with 8 stage columns.
- Cards can be dragged between stages (mock state update, no persistence required).
- Clicking a card opens the Opportunity Detail drawer.
- Toggle between Kanban and Table views works.
- Filter by stage and search by company/title works.
- `APPROVED`/`REJECTED` columns are visually distinct (terminal state styling).
